      },
      "date": "2017-02-28 23:47:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames (x2) and Chris, we are 100% dependent on Cray/ORNL to do inspections of GNILND code.  Could you please inspect this so the patch isn't stuck in Gerrit forever.  Due to this patch having a different Author and Committer, it will need +1 from both of you to land.\n\nIdeally, patches like this would include some kind of comment indicating whether this is just updating the Lustre master code to match your tree (and is already in production), or if it is new development and needs more serious review.\n\nIf this is just bringing the master gnilnd code inline with the Cray production code, I think I'd be willing to rubber-stamp an inspection to get it landed, barring some major code faux-pas that is visible to the non-GNI layman.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
